    /// Borrow-encoded SMEMBERS fast path: streams the set straight into `out`
    /// (RESP2 array `*N` / RESP3 set `~N` header + one bulk string per member)
    /// with NO `Vec<Vec<u8>>` materialization and NO `Vec<RespFrame>` — the read
    /// counterpart of the GET fast path, eliminating two copies of every member
    /// on large SMEMBERS replies. Mirrors the generic path's bookkeeping exactly:
    /// the shared `plain_borrowed_default_key_read_allows` gate (falls back to
    /// generic dispatch when tracking/monitor/multi/etc. are active), keyspace
    /// hit/miss + LFU + touch inside `smembers_borrow_scan`, and the
    /// slowlog/latency/histogram metrics. Returns `None` to fall back.
    /// (frankenredis: SMEMBERS borrow-encode)
