    /// (frankenredis-6s9dx) Conservative borrowed WRITE fast path for the no-option
    /// `COPY source destination` (same DB, no REPLACE). Mirrors the generic
    /// copy_cmd: `store.copy(.., replace=false, ..)` records the source keyspace
    /// lookup, returns 0 when the source is missing or the destination exists,
    /// else copies and returns 1 → `Integer`. Defers (None) when source ==
    /// destination so the generic path emits the exact `ERR source and destination
    /// objects are the same`. The gate requires db0, so the cluster cross-DB reject
    /// (which only fires for non-zero DBs) is a no-op here and matches generic.
